data.description: Assume the VA mortgage at 5.625%!!!! This seller has a VA loan you can assume and it makes the payment similar to a $397k purchase price. Come see this meticulously maintained home in the community of Stonehaven, which is served by Boerne ISD! The house is situated on an oversize corner lot on a cul-de-sac, and sits atop a ridge which lends to amazing sunrise views and wonderful evening breezes. As you walk in the front door of this hill country home, you enter an open-concept Great Room with tile flooring throughout and full of natural light, where the Kitchen, Dining Room, and Living Room blend together creating a spacious, yet cozy gathering space for quality time with family and friends. The kitchen is appointed with granite countertops, 42" upper cabinets, a huge island, stainless steel appliances, and a gas stove which is ideal for the family chef. Just off the Great Room, you'll find the Owner's Retreat with bay window and a bathroom featuring shaver height dual vanity, a glass-enclosed shower, and a garden tub which all create a tranquil setting. The home is a split floor plan design with two additional bedrooms, bathroom, office, and a dedicated laundry room. The backyard has been graded with a gravel patio ideal for a fire pit and other outdoor activities. Located near Leon Spring, it's just a short drive to both San Antonio and Boerne by easy access to IH-10. Major conveniences like HEB and Wal-Mart are located nearby, as well as fine dining, city parks, medical centers, and other important amenities. Come and tour this stunning home today!
